The paper deals with the structure of solution sets of polynomials modulo composite numbers, which is a topic in number theory (cs.NT). The paper also mentions the relevance of these polynomials in computational complexity lower bound frontiers (cs.CC) and in the simulation of quantum circuits (cs.SC). The paper also discusses the divisibility bounds of the solution sets, which is a topic in discrete mathematics (cs.DM). Finally, the paper provides some prospective applications of the research, which could potentially fall under the category of computer science theory (cs.DS).
